The foundation operates the Tiger Woods Learning Center, a $50-million, 35,000-square-foot (3,300Â m2) facility in Anaheim, California, providing college-access programs for underserved youth.[187][189][191] The TWLC opened in 2006 and features seven classrooms, extensive multi-media facilities and an outdoor golf teaching area.[187] The center has since expanded to four additional campuses: two in Washington, D.C.; one in Philadelphia; and one in Stuart, Florida.[191]
